  "text": "These results also are in accordance to previous findings of a U-shaped amygdala activation to both highly pleasant and unpleasant sensory stimuli [CITATION_1] Small et al., 2003) , which convey higher levels of activation than neutral stimuli. These results may hold relevance for visual face processing as the amygdala is known to enhance visual cortical processing for expressive faces [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
